I pick up food from this spot 4 - 5 times a week.  The owner is the nicest guy and always cooking up something delicious.  Not only is the pizza / chicken rolls really good, but my favorite part of Tony Pepperoni is the steam table.  Tony cooks up all kinds of different, unique food you dont typically see in a pizza joint.  Whether its peach reduction baked chicken or a nice marsala, everything is always delicious.  Prices are also very fair for what you get.  Definitely one of my favorites.

Tony P is a beacon of hope that good pizza is still here in Brooklyn. I'm not saying that no other pizzeria is doing it right it's just that, the quality of some of the places I enjoyed has slipped in recent years. And I was starting to worry that people had forgotten or stopped caring. Tony cares and they are doing just right. Quality ingredients, excellent crust, and a solid understanding of toppings makes them a can't miss.
